        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>
Spectral Setup:  We specify one 1.8 GHz band devoted to the continuum. to be observed with ~1.5 km/s spectral resolution.  These bands include the brightest 0.85 mm lines expected from an RSG envelope such as HCN, HCO+, CS, and CO   

Lines to be observed include:  12CO J=3-2, HCN J=4-3, HCO+ J=4-3, and CS J=7-6.  

A full bandwidth of ~8 GHz is needed to cover as many available molecular tracers as possible and to maximize continuum sensitivity. 

</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>To resolve the ring, an angular resolution of 1" is required.  At this resolution, ALMA has about 10 beams along the ring.  The largest angular scale is about 7 to 10".    For 85 K dust the expected flux per beam is about 0.3 mJy.  Thus, a continuum sensitivity of 0.07 mJy in a 1 beam is required.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Infrared observations indicate a minimum gas mass (assuming gas-to-dust ratio of 100) of 0.5 to 1 Solar mass.   Extrapolating to 350 GHz, at D = 7 kpc, an envelope containing  1 Solar mass of  gas is expected to produce a total flux = 1.4 to  4 mJy for a dust temperature of 20 K.  Mid-IR observations show that the inner edge of the 5 radius ring has a dust temperature of  85 K.  If most of the gas is in a compact ring, or if the dispersed dust is this warm, the expect continuum flux from dust is  9 to 24 mJy.

The corresponding spectral line sensitivity is about 30 mK.  At this sensitivity, CO will be detected with high signal-to noise for normal ISM abundance of 7e-5.  A 20 mK requirement enables a sensitive search.  

</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We need aspectal resolution of order 1 km/s.   To get the continuum sensitivity, we need the full bandwidth offered by ALMA of nearly 8 GHz.  The envelope the star and ring may wll contain other molecules such as SO2 and SiC2 that may provide useful constraints on the gas kinematics and chemistry.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_HIGH_DATA_RATE</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
